.SH NAME
dots-add - Copy a file or directory into the active profile


.SH SYNOPSIS
\fBdots add [PATH] [flags]\fP


.SH DESCRIPTION
Copy a file or directory from the home directory into the active profile and update the profile tracking database. Directory adds also record the directory as a tracked root so future new files under it appear in status. Tracked directory roots may be nested. PATH defaults to the current directory. Paths inside any configured dots repo are refused. --dry-run lists the files and directory roots that would be added without copying files or updating the database.


.SH OPTIONS
\fB--dry-run\fP[=false]
	show what would be added without changing files

.PP
\fB-h\fP, \fB--help\fP[=false]
	help for add


.SH OPTIONS INHERITED FROM PARENT COMMANDS
\fB--config\fP=""
	config file path (overrides DOTS_CONFIG; default $XDG_CONFIG_HOME/dots/config.toml or ~/.config/dots/config.toml)

.PP
\fB--profile\fP=""
	profile name (overrides DOTS_PROFILE and default_profile)


.SH SEE ALSO
\fBdots(1)\fP


